
                                            The first lady arrives in Japan on Sunday for a two-day visit with President Donald Trump.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - An all-female squad of officers in Tokyo has been put together to protect us first lady Melania Trump.  The first lady arrives in Japan on Sunday for a two-day visit with President Donald Trump.  The Japanese unit used for this trip was initially put together as part of preparation and training for the 2020 Summer Olympic Games, which will be held in Tokyo.